main event: Aircrew members observed a gray saucer-shaped object stationary at 23,000 feet while flying near Houlton, Maine.
interesting points: The object was observed for 4 minutes,The aircrew attempted to intercept the object but could not close the distance,The object was flying at an indicated air speed of 325 knots,The aircrew reported that the object had no visible means of propulsion,Venus was considered a possible explanation for the sighting.
witness description: Aircrew members from an F-94 aircraft
